<p>I know this might <a href="http://bl.ocks.org/marcoslin/b59cfa9a9a44bde04f9f" rel="nofollow">get an answer here</a>, however that goes more for <strong><em>lazy loading</em></strong> implementation itself.</p>  <p>So, this is a typical <code>UI-Router</code> config block:</p>  <pre><code>app.config(function($stateProvider, $urlRouterProvider, $injector) {     $stateProvider         .state('home', {             url: '/home',             templateUrl: 'view_home.html',  // Actually SHOULD BE result of a XHR request ....             controller: 'HomeCtrl'         }); }); </code></pre>  <p>But what if I want to load such <code>templateUrl</code> when it's requested (<code>$stageChangeStart</code>) and it would be AJAX request based.</p>  <p>How should it be implemented? How are LARGE angular applications dealing with this?</p>